---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import BrandBranchesGrid from '../../components/BrandBranchesGrid.astro';
import { MAIN_PHONE, MAIN_PHONE_TEL } from '../../data/branches';

const title = "GE Monogram Refrigerator Repair Los Angeles — Same Day";
const description = "GE Monogram refrigerator repair across SoCal, 36\" Column built-in, Statement/Minimalist, integrated panel. Haier-owned luxury. $89 dx.";
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/ge-monogram-refrigerator-repair/";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "GE Monogram, GE Café, and GE Profile all say GE, which one do we have, and does it matter?",
    a: "It matters a lot for service. All three are GE Appliances brands (all Haier-owned since 2016), but they're positioned at very different price points and spec tiers. GE Monogram is the ultra-luxury tier ($5,000–$25,000 per appliance), the built-in Column refrigerator, Statement Collection trim, Minimalist design line. GE Café is the style-first premium tier ($2,500–$8,000), customizable hardware finishes, French Door, Wi-Fi integration, Matte Black / Matte White aesthetic. GE Profile is the feature-focused mid-premium tier ($1,500–$5,000), Counter-Depth French Door, Full-Width Freezer Drawer signature, SmartHQ Wi-Fi. The model number on the interior plate tells you which: ZIS, ZISS, ZIC prefixes on Monogram; CWE, CFE, CVE prefixes on Café; PWE, PFE, PVD prefixes on Profile. Our techs confirm the tier before quoting because the parts, platforms, and service protocols differ. Monogram's Column refrigerator is exclusive to Monogram, not available in Café or Profile."
  },
  {
    q: "Haier owns GE Appliances now, is that a problem for Monogram service?",
    a: "Not a problem, and on the parts-availability side, actually an advantage. Haier (the Chinese appliance conglomerate) acquired GE Appliances in 2016 for about $5.4 billion. GE Appliances runs as a US subsidiary, still headquartered at Appliance Park in Louisville, Kentucky, still manufacturing many models in the US, still staffed by the legacy GE engineering and service operation. The Haier backing brought significant capital investment into GE Appliances' parts distribution, which has improved service-parts lead times for Monogram and the rest of the GE luxury line. Practically for our LA service work: Monogram parts flow through the GE Appliances US parts channel, typical 1–2 weeks on standard items through the national warehouse network. The Haier ownership doesn't change how we diagnose or service a Monogram fridge; the hardware architecture and service protocols are unchanged from pre-2016. It changes the corporate backing and the forward-investment posture, both positive for long-term parts support."
  },
  {
    q: "Our Monogram is the 36-inch Column, what should we know about service on that SKU specifically?",
    a: "The Monogram 36-inch Column refrigerator is the flagship luxury SKU, direct competitor to Sub-Zero 648PRO and Thermador Freedom columns. Panel-ready or stainless finish, TwinChill dual-evaporator architecture (separate evaporators for fresh-food and freezer zones, for better humidity control), variable-speed compressor, integrated ice-maker on select configurations. Service considerations specific to Monogram Column: (1) panel-ready installs require the Monogram offset gauge for hinge alignment work, panel-weight adjustment is critical and often missed on non-Monogram-trained techs; (2) the TwinChill dual-evaporator architecture means two separate defrost cycles, diagnostic faults can be specific to one evaporator rather than whole-system; (3) factory parts for the Column SKUs flow through the Monogram-specific channel within GE Appliances, with 1–2 week standard lead. Our techs carry the Monogram service manuals, diagnostic interface, and platform-specific training."
  },
  {
    q: "What is TwinChill and how does it differ from conventional refrigeration?",
    a: "TwinChill is Monogram's dual-evaporator architecture, two separate refrigeration-cycle evaporators, one dedicated to the fresh-food compartment and one dedicated to the freezer compartment, rather than the single-evaporator-with-damper architecture that mainstream refrigerators use. The advantage: the fresh-food compartment maintains higher humidity (because cold air isn't shared with and dried out by the freezer), and food stored in the fresh-food zone stays fresher longer. This is a Sub-Zero-class refrigeration architecture and it's one of the specific reasons the Monogram Column competes directly with Sub-Zero and Thermador Freedom. Service implication: with two evaporators, a defrost fault or fan fault can affect one compartment without the other, we diagnose each evaporator independently rather than assuming whole-system failure. Our service on a Monogram \"freezer isn't cold enough but fresh-food is fine\" call runs differently than the same symptom on a single-evap architecture; we isolate to the freezer-side evap first."
  },
  {
    q: "Do you service the Monogram Statement Collection and Minimalist design options?",
    a: "Yes. Statement Collection and Minimalist are Monogram's trim and handle-design variants within the same underlying refrigerator architecture. Statement Collection uses curved-profile hardware, industrial-professional visual language, and brass, stainless, or brushed hardware accents. Minimalist strips trim detail back to flush surfaces, subtle reveal gaps, and truly integrated architecture, meant to fully disappear into modern cabinetry. Service-side: the refrigeration architecture is identical between the two design lines; trim hardware and handle replacement parts differ. Our techs carry Statement and Minimalist specific hardware replacement items; damage to specific trim elements is sourced through the GE Appliances Monogram parts channel. Lead times 1–2 weeks on standard hardware."
  },
  {
    q: "Our Monogram French Door built-in has an ice-maker fault, what's the usual service path?",
    a: "Monogram built-in French Door ice-makers use the Monogram-specific ice production module with TwinChill-compatible refrigeration. Common fault chain on LA hard-water households: fill valve scales, flow drops, ice-mold fills partially, module cycles inconsistently. Diagnostic: verify inlet water pressure, inspect and descale the water path, test the fill-valve solenoid, check the ice-maker module thermistor and ejector motor. Standard descaling + valve service $280–$440. Full module replacement $480–$760 depending on SKU. The Monogram ice-maker architecture revised in 2020 with improved scale tolerance; if your unit is 2017–2019, the revised module is sometimes worth considering for households producing heavy ice in hard-water zip codes (Encino, Sherman Oaks, Tarzana, Calabasas, Pasadena)."
  },
  {
    q: "What does GE Monogram refrigerator repair cost in LA?",
    a: "Residential diagnostic is $89, waived when you authorize the repair. Common Monogram bands: door gasket (Column) $280–$460; door gasket (built-in French Door) $240–$420; hinge re-shim and alignment $260–$440 (Monogram offset gauge required); TwinChill evaporator-specific defrost service $300–$540; Statement/Minimalist trim hardware replacement, quoted individually; condenser fan motor $280–$480; evaporator fan $260–$440; main control board $520–$820; variable-speed compressor replacement (post-warranty) $1,200–$2,100; ice-maker fill valve + descaling $280–$440; ice-maker module replacement $480–$760. Parts lead times 1–2 weeks through GE Appliances Monogram channel; 3–4 weeks for Statement Collection specific trim items. Factory warranty coverage on current Monogram is 2 years full parts and labor, 5 years sealed-system parts; we coordinate warranty claims when in-scope."
  },
  {
    q: "Sub-Zero vs Monogram Column, for a client deciding at point of purchase, what do you see in the field?",
    a: "Both are excellent; here's what our techs observe across hundreds of LA service calls on each. Sub-Zero has the longest legacy parts-support track record (2025 is 80 years of Sub-Zero, family-owned by the Bakke family since 1945) and the strongest LA regional parts supply (often same-day or next-day from regional stock to Bel Air and Beverly Hills). Monogram is the ultra-luxury alternative from a US-manufactured product with the Haier-backed GE Appliances parts distribution, strong forward investment, improving service infrastructure, and typically priced 10–15% below Sub-Zero for comparable column specs. For 20-plus-year ownership commitment with serviceable legacy, Sub-Zero wins. For contemporary luxury at slightly lower price with strong current parts chain, Monogram competes well. Our team services both equally; the architect or designer selection often follows personal preference rather than technical superiority of one over the other."
  },
  {
    q: "Is Monogram manufactured in the US or in China under Haier?",
    a: "Primarily in the US, Appliance Park in Louisville, Kentucky. Haier's 2016 acquisition of GE Appliances didn't relocate manufacturing; the US plants continue to produce the Monogram lineup (and the broader GE Appliances residential product range). Haier's investment since 2016 has actually expanded US manufacturing footprint at several of the Appliance Park and related US facilities. So when you buy Monogram, you're buying a US-manufactured luxury refrigerator under the broader Haier corporate umbrella, engineered and assembled in Kentucky. This distinguishes Monogram from some other Haier-brand products (like certain Haier-branded appliances) that are manufactured in China for global markets. For service, it means US parts chain, US manufacturing QC history, and the Louisville engineering team reachable through the Monogram service channel."
  },
  {
    q: "Are your techs factory-certified on Monogram specifically?",
    a: "We service Monogram as part of our luxury brand scope. Our techs are trained on the Monogram-specific platforms (Column refrigerator, built-in French Door, TwinChill dual-evaporator architecture, Statement/Minimalist hardware). Factory-authorized Monogram service in the US runs through GE Appliances' service network plus authorized independent service partners. For units still in factory warranty, factory-authorized service is generally the right path, call GE Monogram customer service or factory-authorized partners to preserve warranty coverage. For out-of-warranty service, our team handles repairs with genuine Monogram parts through the GE Appliances parts channel. Our dispatcher navigates warranty-status check at the initial call."
  },

    {
      q: "Where can I find the official GE manual or warranty information?",
      a: `Our technicians work independently of GE's factory service network - we're often faster and available same-day in Southern California.`
    },
  ];

const schemaJsons = [
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "LocalBusiness",
    "@id": canonical + "#business",
    "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair, GE Monogram Refrigerator Service",
    "image": "https://samedayappliance.repair/images/same-day-appliance-repair.png",
    "url": canonical,
    "telephone": MAIN_PHONE_TEL,
    "priceRange": "$$$$",
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Service",
    "serviceType": "GE Monogram Refrigerator Repair",
    "provider": { "@id": canonical + "#business" },
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ],
    "description": "GE Monogram refrigerator repair across Southern California, LA, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, Riverside. 36-inch Column built-in, Statement Collection and Minimalist design lines, built-in French Door, TwinChill dual-evaporator service, variable-speed compressor. Haier-owned GE Appliances since 2016, US-manufactured Louisville KY. $89 residential diagnostic waived with repair.",
    "offers": {
      "@type": "Offer",
      "priceSpecification": {
        "@type": "PriceSpecification",
        "price": "89.00",
        "priceCurrency": "USD",
        "description": "Residential diagnostic fee, waived with repair"
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": faqs.map(f => ({
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": f.q,
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": f.a }
    }))
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Brands", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "GE Monogram", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/ge-monogram/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 4, "name": "GE Monogram Refrigerator Repair", "item": canonical }
    ]
  }
];
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>
  <Fragment slot="head-scripts">
    {schemaJsons.map((schema) => (
      <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />
    ))}
  </Fragment>

  <div class="call-banner">
    <div class="wrap">
      <span>Monogram Column or built-in down? Same-day service across LA:</span>
      <a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="phone-lg">{MAIN_PHONE}</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="hero"><div class="wrap">
          <div class="crumb"><a href="/">Home</a> › <a href="/brands/">Brands</a> › GE Monogram › Refrigerator Repair</div>
          <h1>GE Monogram Refrigerator Repair</h1>
          <p class="lede">
            GE Monogram is the ultra-luxury tier of GE Appliances, the Column built-in refrigerator, Statement
            Collection and Minimalist design lines, TwinChill dual-evaporator architecture, US-manufactured at
            Louisville's Appliance Park, now backed by Haier's 2016 acquisition investment. Our techs service the
            full Monogram lineup across Bel Air, Pacific Palisades, Beverly Hills, Hollywood Hills, and the
            Westside on LA's side, plus Newport Coast and Pelican Hill in OC, Westlake Village and Hidden Hills
            in Ventura, and the Rancho Cucamonga and Temecula wine-country estate corridors in the IE, the
            architect-spec homes where Monogram was the chosen luxury alternative to Sub-Zero. Same-day dispatch
            across all 5 counties, $89 residential diagnostic waived with the repair.
          </p>
          <div class="hero-cta">
            <a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="btn btn-primary">Call {MAIN_PHONE}</a>
            <a href="#book" class="btn btn-ghost">Request a Visit</a>
          </div>
          <ul class="hero-facts">
            <li><b>Column Built-In specialty</b>, Monogram offset gauge, panel-ready shim protocol</li>
            <li><b>TwinChill dual-evaporator diagnostic</b>, isolate faults to fresh-food vs freezer zone</li>
            <li><b>US-manufactured (Louisville) / Haier-backed parts chain</b>, 1–2 week standard</li>
            <li><b>$89 residential diagnostic</b>, waived when you authorize the repair</li>
          </ul>
        </div></section>

  <BrandBranchesGrid />

  <section class="trust-bar">
    <div class="wrap">
      <span>BHGS #A49573 · Insured</span>
      <span>Same-day in 5 SoCal counties</span>
      <span>Residential diagnostic $89 · waived with repair</span>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap narrow">
      <h2>Monogram across Southern California, the GE luxury alternative to Sub-Zero</h2>
      <p>
        GE Monogram is the ultra-luxury tier of the GE Appliances brand family, positioned explicitly against
        Sub-Zero, Thermador Freedom, and Miele MasterCool in the built-in column refrigerator category. Price
        point runs $5,000 to $25,000 per appliance depending on configuration and trim. Our Monogram service
        calls concentrate in architect-spec kitchens from the early 2000s onward across the LA Westside and
        Hollywood Hills, the Newport Coast / Pelican Hill / Shady Canyon OC luxury corridor, the Westlake Village
        / Hidden Hills Conejo Valley estate market, and the Rancho Cucamonga / Temecula wine-country IE estate
        corridor, kitchens where the owner or designer chose Monogram over Sub-Zero, often for the
        US-manufactured story, the broader GE Appliances parts chain, or a 10–15% price advantage on comparable
        column spec.
      </p>
      <p>
        The Haier acquisition in 2016 was a corporate event, not an engineering relocation. GE Appliances continues
        to operate from Appliance Park in Louisville, Kentucky, with US manufacturing maintained and in several
        cases expanded under Haier's forward investment. For Monogram specifically, the Haier era has improved
        parts distribution and service-infrastructure funding, practical effects visible to our service operation
        in shorter parts lead times and better technical documentation access. The Monogram architecture, service
        protocols, and field failure patterns are unchanged from the pre-2016 era; what's changed is the forward-
        looking investment posture of the parent company. That's net-positive for long-term ownership.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section alt">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>Monogram refrigerator failures our techs see most often in LA</h2>
      <p class="intro">
        Pattern data from our Monogram coverage across LA. Column built-in and built-in French Door configurations
        dominate dispatch; pattern data skews toward installation-era alignment, TwinChill-side evaporator service,
        and standard luxury-column sensor drift.
      </p>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>TwinChill freezer-side fault, fresh-food fine but freezer warm</h3>
        <p>
          Monogram's dual-evaporator architecture means a fault on one evaporator circuit can affect one compartment
          without the other. Most common: freezer-side evap defrost cycle incomplete (defrost heater weak,
          thermostat stuck) leaving frost on the evaporator and reducing cooling capacity. Diagnostic isolates to
          freezer-side evap first. Defrost heater service $300–$520. Full freezer-side evap work $420–$680.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Column panel alignment drift on heavy cabinet panels</h3>
        <p>
          Panel-ready Column installs with heavy custom-hardwood panels: closer tension not adjusted for panel
          weight at commissioning, reveal gap widens at 12–24 months. Fix is hinge re-shim plus closer tension
          adjustment with Monogram offset gauge. 90-minute typical service.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Ice-maker mineral buildup, Southern California hard-water pattern</h3>
        <p>
          Built-in French Door and Column ice-makers across Encino, Sherman Oaks, Tarzana, Calabasas, Pasadena,
          Newport Beach, Westlake Village, and Rancho Cucamonga / Temecula households scale fill valves over
          6–12 months, and on the order of 4–6 months in the hardest IE districts. Standard descale + valve service $280–$440. Monogram
          revised module on 2020+ units with improved scale tolerance; older SKU module swap $480–$760.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Statement Collection / Minimalist trim hardware replacement</h3>
        <p>
          Damage to the signature Statement Collection (curved handles, brass/brushed/stainless trim) or Minimalist
          (flush profile) hardware requires design-specific replacement parts through the Monogram parts channel.
          1–2 week standard lead, 3–4 weeks on niche Statement-specific items. Repair labor only once parts
          arrive, we coordinate ordering to minimize visit count.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Sensor drift on multi-zone built-in French Door</h3>
        <p>
          Monogram built-in French Door units with multi-zone cooling occasionally show sensor drift producing
          compartment-specific temperature misread. Diagnostic via Monogram service interface; sensor replacement
          $180–$340.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Variable-speed compressor, running solid in the installed base</h3>
        <p>
          Monogram's variable-speed compressor platform has been running well across our 2015–2025 SoCal coverage
          window, no systemic failure patterns have surfaced. Post-warranty compressor replacement on Monogram
          $1,200–$2,100 depending on SKU and refrigerant, but the work is uncommon in our dispatch mix. Sealed-
          system integrity on Monogram is a genuine strength.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>GE Monogram US refrigerator lines we service</h2>
      <p class="intro">
        Monogram residential refrigeration centers on the Column platform and built-in French Door, with Statement
        Collection and Minimalist as design variants within the architecture. US-manufactured at GE Appliances'
        Louisville facilities.
      </p>
      <div class="model-grid">
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>36" Column Refrigerator (ZIR/ZIC prefix)</h3>
          <p>Flagship Monogram column. Panel-ready or stainless. TwinChill dual-evaporator, variable-speed
          compressor, Statement Collection or Minimalist trim. Direct Sub-Zero 648PRO and Thermador Freedom
          competitor.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>36" Column Freezer (ZIF prefix)</h3>
          <p>Matched Monogram freezer column. Paired with refrigerator column for full column-pair installs.
          Shared Monogram architecture; ice-maker integration on select configurations.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Built-In French Door (ZWE/ZWS prefix)</h3>
          <p>Counter-depth built-in French Door configuration. Flush with cabinetry. TwinChill architecture,
          Statement or Minimalist trim hardware options, in-door ice-and-water on select SKUs.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Statement Collection design language</h3>
          <p>Curved-profile handle hardware, industrial-professional visual cues, brass or brushed-stainless trim
          options. Statement is the more-traditional luxury look within the Monogram family.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Minimalist design language</h3>
          <p>Flush surfaces, tight reveal gaps, pared-back hardware. Designed to disappear into modern cabinetry.
          Same refrigeration architecture as Statement; the design treatment differs.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>TwinChill dual-evaporator platform</h3>
          <p>Dual refrigeration-cycle evaporators for independent fresh-food and freezer cooling. Higher fresh-food
          humidity, food stays fresher longer. Service-diagnostic implication: each evaporator circuit is
          independently serviceable.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section alt">
    <div class="wrap narrow">
      <h2>Monogram vs Sub-Zero vs Thermador, the architect-spec column conversation</h2>
      <p>
        Three brands our Monogram clients typically considered: Sub-Zero (most common cross-shop), Thermador
        Freedom Collection, and occasionally Miele MasterCool. Here's the honest positioning read from the field.
      </p>
      <p>
        <b>Sub-Zero</b>, Wisconsin-built, Bakke family since 1945, strongest Southern California parts chain and longest legacy
        support. Conservative stainless-or-panel aesthetic. See
        <a href="/brands/sub-zero-refrigerator-repair/">Sub-Zero refrigerator repair</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        <b>Thermador Freedom Collection</b>, BSH German parent, shared parts with Bosch, strong column-width
        flexibility. See <a href="/brands/thermador-refrigerator-repair/">Thermador refrigerator repair</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        <b>GE Monogram</b>, US-manufactured in Louisville (unchanged through Haier 2016 acquisition), TwinChill
        dual-evaporator architecture, Statement or Minimalist design treatment, 10–15% below Sub-Zero on
        comparable column spec. Best pick when the household wants American-manufactured luxury with a strong
        forward parts chain under Haier backing, or specifically values the TwinChill architecture's humidity
        advantage. Cross-link sibling pages: <a href="/brands/ge-cafe-refrigerator-repair/">GE Café
        refrigerator repair</a> (style-first premium tier), <a href="/brands/ge-profile-refrigerator-repair/">GE
        Profile refrigerator repair</a> (feature-focused mid-premium tier), and
        <a href="/brands/ge-refrigerator-repair/">GE refrigerator repair</a> (base GE lineup).
      </p>
      <p>
        None is objectively better; all three are excellent luxury refrigerators. Our team services all three
        equally with platform-specific training.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>What GE Monogram refrigerator repair costs in LA</h2>
      <p class="intro">Parts pricing in line with luxury built-in peers; lead times 1–2 weeks through GE Appliances
      Monogram channel. Residential diagnostic $89, waived with repair.</p>
      <table class="price-table">
        <tr><th>Service</th><th>Typical Range</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
        <tr><td>Residential diagnostic</td><td>$89</td><td>Flat, waived if repair is authorized same visit</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Door gasket (Column)</td><td>$280 – $460</td><td>Column profile, panel-weight shim</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Door gasket (built-in French Door)</td><td>$240 – $420</td><td>Counter-depth built-in profile</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Hinge re-shim + alignment</td><td>$260 – $440</td><td>Monogram offset gauge required</td></tr>
        <tr><td>TwinChill freezer-side defrost service</td><td>$300 – $540</td><td>Evaporator-specific defrost cycle</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Sensor replacement</td><td>$180 – $340</td><td>Monogram service interface diagnostic</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Condenser fan motor replacement</td><td>$280 – $480</td><td>Standard Column specs on truck</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Evaporator fan replacement</td><td>$260 – $440</td><td>Either TwinChill evap circuit</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Ice-maker fill valve + descaling</td><td>$280 – $440</td><td>Hard-water SoCal households (esp. IE)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Ice-maker module replacement</td><td>$480 – $760</td><td>Revised module on 2020+ improves scale tolerance</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Main control board replacement</td><td>$520 – $820</td><td>Post-firmware diagnosis</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Statement / Minimalist trim hardware</td><td>Quoted individually</td><td>Design-specific, 1–4 week lead</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Variable-speed compressor (post-warranty)</td><td>$1,200 – $2,100</td><td>Uncommon service on Monogram</td></tr>
      </table>
      <p class="small">
        Broader refrigerator cost reference: our <a href="/price-list/refrigerator-repair-cost/">refrigerator repair
        cost guide</a>. Column built-in-specific scope: <a href="/services/built-in-refrigerator-repair/">built-in
        refrigerator repair</a>. Monogram oven, range, and cooking repair covered on sibling pages, see the
        Monogram <a href="/brands/ge-monogram-refrigerator-repair/">brand hub</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section alt">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>Service areas, where our Monogram calls come from</h2>
      <div class="area-grid">
        <div>
          <h4>Westside (architect-spec kitchens)</h4>
          <p><a href="/beverly-hills/">Beverly Hills</a> · Bel Air · <a href="/brentwood/">Brentwood</a> · <a href="/pacific-palisades/">Pacific Palisades</a> · <a href="/santa-monica/">Santa Monica</a> · <a href="/west-hollywood/">West Hollywood</a></p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4>Hollywood Hills + luxury hillside</h4>
          <p>Hollywood Hills · Laurel Canyon · Nichols Canyon · Mount Olympus · Bird Streets · Outpost Estates</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4>Coastal (Malibu + South Bay)</h4>
          <p><a href="/malibu/">Malibu</a> · Venice · Marina del Rey · Manhattan Beach · Palos Verdes</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4>San Fernando Valley (hard-water ice service)</h4>
          <p><a href="/encino/">Encino</a> · Sherman Oaks · Tarzana · Calabasas · Hidden Hills · Woodland Hills</p>
        </div>
        <div>
